  "issue_number": 14821,
  "issue_title": "Style/IfInsideElse autocorrect moves condition into the wrong place",
  "issue_body": "If an `else` block starts with a comment, `Style/IfInsideElse` should not move that comment down into the following `true` branch of the following condition.\n\n--------\n\n## Steps to reproduce the problem\n\nRun the `Style/IfInsideElse` cop (with autoformatter) on the following:\n\n```ruby\nif cond_a\n  body_a\nelse\n  # Not A!\n  \n  if cond_b\n    body_b\n  else\n    body_c\n  end\nend\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nNo `Style/IfInsideElse` should be triggered, and the autoformatter should leave the code intact.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe code is autocorrected to the following\n\n```ruby\nif cond_a\n  body_a\nelsif cond_b\n  # Not A!\n\n  body_b\nelse\n  body_c\nend\n```\n\nHere, the comment `# Not A!` erroneously is inside the `cond_b` true condition.\n\n```\nUse parallel by default.\nSkipping parallel inspection: only a single file needs inspection\nInspecting 1 file\nScanning /Users/denis/xxxxxxx/ma/blah.rb\nC\n\nOffenses:\n\nblah.rb:1:1: C: [Correctable] Style/FrozenStringLiteralComment: Missing frozen string literal comment.\nif cond_a\n^\nblah.rb:5:1: C: [Correctable] Layout/TrailingWhitespace: Trailing whitespace detected.\nblah.rb:6:3: C: [Correctable] Style/IfInsideElse: Convert if nested inside else to elsif.\n  if cond_b\n  ^^\n\n1 file inspected, 3 offenses detected, 3 offenses autocorrectable\nFinished in 0.26967599987983704 seconds\n```\n\n## RuboCop version\n\n```\n1.82.1 (using Parser 3.3.10.0, Prism 1.8.0, rubocop-ast 1.49.0, analyzing as Ruby 3.3, running on ruby 3.3.6) [arm64-darwin25]\n  - rubocop-factory_bot 2.28.0\n  - rubocop-minitest 0.38.2\n  - rubocop-performance 1.26.1\n  - rubocop-rails 2.34.3\n```\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-28T03:21:47Z",
